  "text": "Hysteroscopy is considered to be the gold standard to diagnose intrauterine pathology. Office HYS is being used increasingly in infertility work-up when TP is not an issue [CITATION_1] . Assessment of TP is not a part of routine hysteroscopic procedure. Adding evaluation of TP to routine HYS could provide several advantages. Our study showed that HCT could give useful information about TP with high sensitivity and moderate specificity compared to LCT.",
